content.text: the current javascript ecosystem has many libraries and frameworks, established programming practices, and substantial usage of javascript outside of web browsers. plus, with the rise of single-page applications and other javascript-heavy websites, several transpilers have been created to aid the development process.[34]javascript is the dominant client-side language of the web, and many websites are script-heavy. thus transpilers have been created to convert code written in other languages, which can aid the development process.[34]
